parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the camshaft seal end plug can cause oil to leak onto the spark plugs and exhaust manifold, leading to smoke emission, oil smell, and potentially causing accidents or engine failure.
symptoms: Smoke coming from underneath the hood
oil leaking onto spark plugs and exhaust manifold
oil accumulation on spark plug wires

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hydraulic lifter system can lead to engine failure, oil sludge build-up, and premature wear of engine components.
Engine oil leaks can cause damage to spark plug wires, spark plug failure, and potentially lead to engine failure or accidents.
Thermostat failure can cause engine overheating, leading to engine damage or failure.

The deterioration of the transmission wire harness can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to accidents or stranding the driver. The excessive heat from the catalytic converter can cause the wire insulation to burn away, leading to electrical issues.
symptoms: The transmission warning lights may not function
and the vehicle may not shift gears properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transfer case can cause the vehicle to lose power and control, leading to accidents. The lack of oil in the transfer case can cause it to overheat and fail.
symptoms: The transfer case may leak oil
and the vehicle may lose power or become difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic transmission can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to accidents or stranding the driver. The transmission may slip or hesitate, making it difficult to control the vehicle.
symptoms: The transmission may slip or hesitate
the check transmission light may come on
and the vehicle may not shift gears properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the gear selection sensor can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to accidents or stranding the driver. The sensor may malfunction, causing the transmission to shift incorrectly.
symptoms: The check transmission light may come on
and the vehicle may not shift gears properly. The error indicator message may indicate a problem with the gear selection sensor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal may feel soft or spongy
the clutch pedal may stick to the floor
and the vehicle may not shift gears properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Speedometer and Engine Check Light Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the speedometer and engine check light can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents.
symptoms: the engine check light may come on intermittently

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the four-wheel drive system can cause the vehicle to lose traction and control, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle may not engage in four-wheel drive mode
and the vehicle may lose traction and control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the gear shift knob can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The gear shift knob may break or become difficult to use
making it difficult to shift gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause a range of problems, including power window malfunctions, electrical fires, and vehicle stalling, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: smoke coming from under the power window control

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Alternator regulator failure can cause electrical system failures, leading to vehicle stalling, electrical fires, and damage to other components.
Door locking system failures can cause doors to become stuck or inoperable, making it difficult or impossible to exit the vehicle in an emergency.
symptoms: Rear doors do not open from inside or outside
water running down inside the door and corroding the locking controls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to address recall issues can lead to electrical system failures, vehicle stalling, and other problems that can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Dealership unwilling to perform recall work
